PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776409519
OL,3,CMajor seafront hotel to no longer
OL,4,Chouse asylum seekers
OL,6,FA major seafront hotel will no longer
OL,7,Fbe used to house asylum seekers, a
OL,8,Flocal MP has confirmed.
OL,10,FBlackpool South MP Chris Webb pledged
OL,11,Fto end the use of the Metropole Hotel
OL,12,Ffor housing asylum seekers, and has
OL,13,Fnow received assurances from the
OL,14,FGovernment that it will return to
OL,15,Fnormal use.
OL,17,FThe hotel, which sits on Blackpool's
OL,18,Fseafront, has been housing asylum
OL,19,Fseekers since 2021 despite pledges at
OL,20,Fthe time that it would only be used
OL,21,Ffor three months.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
