FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776409519
OL,3,CMajor seafront hotel to no longer
OL,4,Chouse asylum seekers
OL,6,FAround 140`220 people were initially
OL,7,Fmoved into the hotel by the Home
OL,8,FOffice due to "unprecedented demand"
OL,9,Ffor accommodation, despite objections
OL,10,Ffrom local officials
OL,12,FMr Webb has been a long-standing
OL,13,Fopponent of its use for migrant
OL,14,Ffamilies, frequently urging the Home
OL,15,FOffice to close it.
OL,17,FOn Tuesday 14 April 2026, the
OL,18,FGovernment announced 11 of the 196
OL,19,Fasylum hotels have been permanently
OL,20,Fclosed sparking renewed calls to take
OL,21,Faction on the Metropole Hotel.
OL,26,@pD@OOUpD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
