FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776409519
OL,3,CMajor seafront hotel to no longer
OL,4,Chouse asylum seekers
OL,6,FIn a letter to the Minister of State
OL,7,Ffor Border Security Alex Norris, Chris
OL,8,FWebb said: "As a historic and locally-
OL,9,Flisted venue, the Metropole long
OL,10,Fserved as a vital part of the local
OL,11,Ftourism industry, providing
OL,12,Faccommodation for visitors and
OL,13,Fsupporting the accommodation for our
OL,14,Ftown.
OL,16,F"The use of the Metropole as an asylum
OL,17,Fhotel was originally presented as a
OL,18,Fshort term measure under the previous
OL,19,FConservative government but is now
OL,20,Fentering is fourth year.
OL,26,@xD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776409519
OL,3,CMajor seafront hotel to no longer
OL,4,Chouse asylum seekers
OL,6,F"Blackpool is the most deprived local
OL,7,Fauthority in England, with the
OL,8,FMetropole located on he edge of he
OL,9,Fsecond most deprived neighbourhood in
OL,10,Fthe country, right on Blackpool's
OL,11,Fhistoric seafront."
OL,13,FIn response, the Labour MP says he has
OL,14,Fbeen told by the Government that from
OL,15,FJuly the hotel will no longer be used
OL,16,Fto house asylum seekers
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
