OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1776409519
OL,3,CMajor seafront hotel to no longer
OL,4,Chouse asylum seekers
OL,6,FThose currently staying at the
OL,7,FMetropole will be moved into "more
OL,8,Fappropriate" asylum accommodation or
OL,9,Fex-military bases outside of Blackpool.
OL,11,FThe Labour government's push to reduce
OL,12,Fthe number of asylum hotels in use
OL,13,Fmakes up part of its plege to stop
OL,14,Fusing hotels in this way by July 2029.
OL,16,FBut the Conservatives said the
OL,17,Fgovernment was "shunting people from
OL,18,Fhotels into residential apartments to
OL,19,Fhide what is going on".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
